#!/usr/bin/ocatve# 3. Triangle inequality:# x + y ≤ x + y.# (If property 1 is relaxed to require only x ≥ 0 for x = 0, the function is# called a seminorm.) Because a norm is a function whose argument is a vector,# we also often use a functional notation such as ρ(x) to represent a norm.x = 0y = 100ax = [22, 23, 25; 31, 32, 33; 41, 42, 43; 51, 52, 53]if (x + y < x + y)    disp("property 1 is relaxed to require only")else    for ax = x:y        ax    endend    